The paper discusses adversarial training of deep neural nets, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments involve image classification tasks, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses regularization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with adversarial attacks, which are a security concern in cryptography (cs.CR).
